main event: A CDC spotter observed a rocket-shaped object with flaming exhaust moving very fast on October 15, 1952.
interesting points: The object was reported to be rocket-shaped and emitted flaming exhaust., The sighting lasted for about 30 seconds., The object was moving very fast, estimated speed was between 600 to 800 miles an hour., There was no sound associated with the object during the sighting., The sighted object was speculated to possibly be a meteorite or related to satellites or rockets.
